fields.name: Hughes
fields.description:
All queens start on the left.
A player can not end their turn in check.
If a player can not make a valid move their turn is skipped.
Once a player captures an opponents king, they gain control of the defeated opponents turn.

fields.name: Chaos
fields.description:
Pawns move forward diagonally and can attack orthogonally.  

En-Passant is not allowed.

Castling is not allowed.

You can not make a move if your turn would end with you in check.

If you capture an opponents king, you gain control of their turn.

fields.name: 8 handed chess
fields.description:
Queens on the left.
Two teams of two; each player is on a team with the player that is farthest away.
You cannot end your turn in check. If it is not possible for you to escape check, your turn is skipped.
When you capture another player's king, you gain control of their turn.

fields.name: Tablut
fields.description:
The king starts on the central square, once it leaves that square;  no other piece may occupy it.

All pieces can move any number of vacant orthogonal spaces.

Pieces are captured if they are surrounded on two sides by an opponent.

Black wins by surrounding the white king on 4 sides.

White wins by moving his king off of the board (there must be a clear path to the dge of the board)
